description: TO APPOINT KEY PITTMAN, A SENATOR FROM NEVADA, AS PRESIDENT PRO TEMPORE, IN PLACE OF ALBERT B. CUMMINS, A SENATOR FROM IOWA.
TO TABLE AN APPEAL FROM THE CHAIR RULING THAT THE MOTION TO DISCHARGE THE COMMITTEE ON WOMAN SUFFRAGE WAS NOT DEBATABLE.

TO AMEND A MOTION TO DISCHARGE THE COMM. ON WOMAN SUFFRAGE FROM FURTHER CONSIDERATION OF H. J. RES. 1, PROPOSING AN AMENDMENT TO THE CONSTITUTION EXTENDING SUFFRAGE TO WOMEN, BY PROVIDING THAT THE COMMITTEE BE DISCHARGED IN 3 DAYS.
TO SUSTAIN THE RULING OF THE CHAIR, MADE DURING DEBATE ON HJR 1, RULING THAT ITS DECISIONS ARE DEBATABLE.

TO TABLE AN AMENDMENT TO AN ORDER PROVIDING THAT THE SENATE CHOOSE MAJORITY CHAIRMAN OF THE SEVERAL COMMITTEES; SAID AMENDMENT PROVIDING THAT THE COMMITTEE CHAIRMAN SHALL BE SELECTED BY A CALL OF THE ROLL.
TO TABLE ON MR. HITCHCOCK'S MOTION TO WITHDRAW THE NAME OF MR. PENROSE AS CHAIRMAN OF THE COMMITTEE ON FINANCE.

TO TABLE MR. HITCHCOCK'S AMENDMENT TO A PROPOSED ORDER FOR ELECTION BY ROLL CALL, WITHOUT DEVISION OF COMMITTEE CHAIRMAN AND MEMBERS.  MR. HITCHCOCK'S AMENDMENT PROVIDES THAT REPUBLICAN MAJORITY ON ANY COMMITTEES SHOULD BE REDUCED TO 2.
TO ADOPT A RESOLUTION PROVIDING THAT INDIVIDUAL CHAIRMEN AS WELL AS MEMBERS OF THE COMMITTEE BE VOTED UPON BY ROLL CALL COLLECTIVELY.
TO ADOPT A RESOLUTION ELECTING BY ROLL CALL, CHAIRMAN AND MEMBERS OF ALL STANDING COMMITTEES OF THE SENATE.
TO AMEND HJR 1 BY RESTRECTING THE RIGHT TO VOTE TO WHITE CITIZENS OF UNITED STATES, REGARDLESS OF SEX.
TO AMEND H. J. RES. 1, BY PROVIDING THAT THE CONSTITUTIONAL AMENDMENT SHALL BE PROPOSED TO SPECIALLY ELECTED STATE CONVENTIONS, RATHER THAN THE LEGISLATIVES THEREOF.
TO AMEND HJR 1, BY GIVING THE VARIOUS STATES THE RIGHT TO ENACT AND ENFORCE LAWS GIVING WOMEN THE RIGHT TO VOTE, INSTEAD OF PROVIDING FOR A CONSTITUTIONAL AMENDMENT.
TO PASS HJR 1.
TO PASS S. RES. 48, A RESOLUTION URGING THE AMERICAN PEACE COMMISSION TO SECURE A HEARING FOR THE REPRESENTATIVES OF THE IRISH REPUBLIC.
TO PERMIT A PRINTING OF A COPY OF THE VERSAILLES TREATY, WHICH THE PRESIDENT OF THE UNITED STATES THOUGHT BEST TO BE WITHHELD FROM THE PUBLIC.
TO PROCEED TO THE READING OF THE VERSAILLES TREATY.
TO RECONSIDER THE QUESTION OF READING THE VERSAILLES TREATY.
TO AMEND HR 3157, A BILL MAKING APPROPRIATIONS FOR THE AGRICULTURAL DEPARTMENT FOR FISCAL 1920, BY INCREASING THE APPROPRIATION FROM $551,280.00 TO $751,280.00.
TO TABLE AN AMENDMENT TO HR 3157, ALLOWING THE MANUFACTURE AND SALE OF WINE AND BEER.
TO SUSPEND PARAGRAPH THREE OF RULE XVI AND THEREBY PERMIT AN AMENDMENT TO HR 3157, REPEALING THE DAYLIGHT SAVING LAW.
TO AMEND HR 3157, BY REPEALING THE DAYLIGHT SAVINGS TIME LAW AND PROVIDING STANDARD TIME FOR THE UNITED STATES.

TO AMEND HR 5227, (41 STAT. 104), THE ARMY APPROPRIATIONS BILL, BY PREVENTING THE AUTHORIZATION OF AN EXPENDITURE OF $3,260,000 FOR THE PURCHASE OF THE DAYTON WRIGHT AIRPLANE FACTORY NEAR DAYTON, OHIO.

TO AMEND HR 5227, BY ELIMINATING PROVISION THAT APPROPRIA- TIONS IN THIS BILL SHALL NOT BE USED TO PAY SALARY OF ANY PERSON SUPERVISING ANOTHER EMPLOYEE OF THE U. S. IF SAID SUPERVISOR USES A STOP WATCH OR ATTEMPTED TO MAKE A TIME STUDY OF EMPLOYEE'S JOB.

TO AMEND HR 5227, BY PROVIDING TO STRIKE A PROVISION THAT GOVERNMENT EMPLOYEES MAY NOT RECEIVE A BONUS OR CASH REWARD, EXCEPT FOR SUGGESTIONS RESULTING IN IMPROVEMENT IN OPERATION OF A GOVERNMENT PLANT.

TO SUSPEND THE RULES IN ORDER TO PROPOSE AN AMENDMENT TO H. R. 5227, SAID AMENDMENT PROVIDING THAT RESTRICTIONS CONCERNING PERSONAL SERVICES AND PER DIEM ALLOWANCES SHALL NOT APPLY TO MONEY APPROPRIATED FOR PURPOSE OF CARRYING OUT EXISTING LAWS RELATING TO SALE OF WAR SUPPLIES.
TO AMEND HR 5227 BY PROVIDING THAT NO CIVILIAN EMPLOYEE OR OFFICER BELOW THE RANK OF MAJOR GENERAL SHALL RECEIVE MORE THAN $12,000 PER ANNUM.

TO AGREE TO THE AMENDMENT OF THE COMMITTEE ON APPROPRIATIONS TO HR 6176, A BILL MAKING SUNDRY CIVIL APPROPRIATIONS FOR FISCAL 1920, BY REDUCING THE APPROPRIATION FOR THE FEDERAL TRADE COMMISSION FROM $1,000,000 TO $900,000.
TO AGREE TO AN AMENDMENT TO HR 6176, REDUCING THE AMOUNT APPROPRIATED FOR THE TARIFF COMMISSION FROM $300,000 TO $200,000.

TO SUSTAIN THE DECISION OF THE CHAIR, MADE DURING DEBATE ON HR 6176, RULING THAT A $50 MILLION APPROPRIATION FOR IRRIGATION IS GENERAL LEGISLATION AND NOT AUTHORIZED BY THIS BILL.  (NO QUORUM VOTING.)
TO SUSTAIN THE DECISION OF THE CHAIR, THAT A PROPOSED $50,000,000 APPROPRIATION FOR RECLAMATION IS GENERAL LEGISLATION AND NOT PROPERLY BEFORE THE SENATE.

TO AMEND HR 7343, (41 STAT. 163, 7/19/19), MAKING APPROPRIA- TIONS FOR SUNDRY CIVIL EXPENSES OF THE GOVERNMENT FOR THE FISCAL YEAR ENDING 1920, BY DECLARING THAT THE STATUS OF PEACE BETWEEN THE FORMER IMPERIAL GERMAN GOVERNMENT AND THE UNITED STATES BEING DECLARED TO EXIST NO PART OF SAID SUM OF $1,730,000, SHALL BE USED IN ENFORCING THE PROVISIONS KNOWN AS THE TRADING-WITH-THE-ENEMY ACT.
TO PASS HR 3854, A BILL REPEALING THE DAYLIGHT SAVING LAW.
TO ADJOURN, MADE DURING CONSIDERATION OF THE SENATE CALENDAR.
TO OVERRIDE THE PRESIDENT'S VETO OF HR 3854, A BILL REPEALING THE DAYLIGHT SAVING LAW.

TO AMEND S 2775, (41STAT. 437, 2/25/20), A BILL PROMOTING THE MINING OF COAL, PHOSPHATE, OIL, GAS AND SODIUM ON PUBLIC DOMAIN, BY RESERVING TO THE GOVERNMENT THE RIGHT AT ALL TIMES TO DETERMINE, FIX, AND CONTROL THE SELLING PRICE OF ALL PRODUCTS DERIVED FROM LANDS LEASED HEREUNDER.

TO AMEND S 2775, A BILL PROMOTING THE MINING OF COAL, PHOSPHATE, OIL, GAS, AND SODIUM ON PUBLIC DOMAIN, BY PROVIDING THAT THE GOVERNMENT SHALL RESERVE AND PROVIDE IN EVERY LEASE OF OIL LANDS THAT THE OWNER AND OPERATOR OF ANY PIPE LINE, SHALL AT REASONABLE RATES AND WITHOUT DISCRIMINA- TION, CONVEY THE OIL OF THE GOVERNMENT OR OF ANY PERSON OR COMPANY.  (NO QUORUM VOTING.)

TO ADOPT AN AMENDMENT OF THE JUDICIARY COMMITTEE TO HR 6810, (41 STAT. 305, 10/28/19), A BILL PROHIBITING INTOXICATING BEVERAGES AND CONTROLLING THE MANUFACTURE AND USE OF ALCOHOL.  THE AMENDMENT PLACES THE BURDEN OF PROOF ON DEFEN- DANTS IN CASES OF UNLAWFUL POSSISSION OR SALE OF INTOSICA- TING LIQUOR.

TO POSTPONE CONSIDERATION OF THE PEACE TREATY WITH GERMANY, TO AFFORD MORE TIME FOR CONSIDERING AN AMENDMENT BARRING THE UNITED STATES FROM VARIOUS COMMISSIONS TO BE PROVIDED FOR CARRYING OUT TREATIES PROVISIONS.

TO TABLE AN APPEAL FROM THE DECISION OF THE CHAIR, DURING DEBATE ON HR 7478, (41STAT. 296, 10/22/19), A BILL AMENDING SECTIONS 5200 AND 5202 OF THE REFISED STATUTES OF THE UNITED STATES IN RELATION TO BILLS OF EXCHANGE, RULING THAT THE ABOVE BILL IS PROPERLY BEFORE THE SENATE.

TO REFER S. RES 186, A RESOLUTION INVESTIGATING REPARTS IN THE PRESS THAT THE POSTMASTER GENERAL HAS BEEN ACTIVELY INTERFERING WITH THE CIVIL SERVICE COMMISSION IN RELATION TO THE EXAMINATION AND CERTIFICATION OF ELIGIBLES FOR POST- MASTER PASTS, TO THE COMMITTEE ON CIVIL SERVICE FOR INVESTIGATION OF THE SAID CHARGES MADE IN THE NEWSPAPER AND MAGAZINES.

TO SUSTAIN THE DECISION OF THE CHAIR, MADE DURING DEBATE ON HR 7478, IN OVERRULING THE POINT OF ORDER THAT THIS BILL IS NOT PROPERLY BEFORE THE SENATE BECAUSE IT HAS NOT ACTED UPON BY COMMITTEE TO WHICH IT WAS REFERRED.
TO AMEND HR 7478, BY REDUCING THE AMOUNT A NATIONAL BANK MAY LOAN TO AN INDIVIDUAL BORROWER ON NOTES SECURED BY SHIPPING DOCUMENTS FROM 25% TO 20%.
TO AMEND THE VERSAILLES TREATY BY STRIKING THE PROVISION ASSOCIATING THE UNITED STATES WITH OTHER POWERS IN DETERMINING THE BOUNDARIES BETWEEN GERMANY AND BELGUIM.
TO AMEND THE VERSAILLES TREATY, BY PROVIDING THAT THE GOVERNING COMMISSION, CREATED BY THE VERSAILLE TREATY, SHALL HAVE ALL POWERS OF GOVERNMENT IN THE TERRITORY OF THE SAAR BASIN.

TO AMEND THE VERSAILLES TREATY, BY ELIMINATING THE PROVISION THAT A TREATY SHALL HEREAFTER BY MADE BETWEEN THE PRINCIPAL ALLIED POWERS, BY WHICH CZECHOSLOVOKIA AGREES TO PROTECT THE INTEREST OF THE INHABITANTS OF THAT STATE, WHO DIFFER FROM THE MAJORITY OF THE POPULIST IN RACE, LANGUAGE OR RELIGION.

TO AMEND THE VERSAILLES TREATY, BY PROVIDING THAT NO REPRESENTATIVE FROM THE UNITED STATES SHALL BE APPOINTED TO THE INTERNATIONAL COMMISSION FOR UPPER SILESIA, AND THAT UPPER SILESIA SHALL BE OCCUPIED BY TROOPS BELONGING TO THE ALLIED AND ASSOCIATED POWERS.

TO AMEND HR 7478, BY PROVIDING THAT THE TOTAL LIABILITIES OF ANY PERSON, CORPORATION, FIRM OR COMPANY TO ANY ASSOCIATION SHALL NOT EXCEED THE PAID IN THE INIMPAIRED CAPITAL STOCK AND SURPLUS OF SUCH AND ASSOCIATION.
TO PASS HR 7478.
TO PASS S 2867, A BILL AUTHORIZING THE PRESIDENT TO PLACE MAJOR GENERAL E. H. CROWDER ON THE RETIRED LIST OF THE ARMY AS A LIEUTENANT GENERAL, WHEN HE RETIRES.
TO ADJOURN DURING DEBATE ON THE VERSAILLES TREATY BECAUSE OF THE LATE HOUR.  (THIS VOTE WAS TAKEN IN LEGISLATIVE SESSION.)

TO AMEND H.J. RES. 151, (41STAT. 350 11/7/19), A RESOLUTION PROVIDING ADDITIONAL COMPENSATION FOR EMPLOYEES OF THE POSTAL SYSTEM, BY INCREASING THE SALARIES AND ALLOWANCES OF FOURTH-CLASS POSTMASTERS FROM 10% TO 15% AND PROVIDING AN ALLOWANCE OF $50 PER QUARTER FOR RENT.
TO AGREE TO SIX AMENDMENTS OF THE COMMITTEE ON FOREIGN RELATIONS, RELATING TO THE VERSAILLES TREATY, GIVING JAPAN THE RIGHTS IN THE PROVINCE OF SHANTUNG HERETOFORE HELD BY GERMANY.

TO AMEND HR 9205, (41 STAT. 327, 11/4/19), A BILL MAKING APPROPRIATIONS FOR SUPPLY DEFICIENCIES IN APPROPRIATIONS FOR THE FISCAL YEAR ENDING JUNE 30, 1920, BY APPROPRIATING $200,000 FOR ENFORCEMENT OF ANTI-TRUST LAWS.

TO AGREE TO THE AMENDMENTS OF THE COMMITTEE ON FOREIGN RELATIONS, RELATING TO THE VERSAILLES TREATY, GIVING THE UNITED STATES VOTES IN THE LEAGUE NUMERICALLY EQUAL TO THE AGGREGATE VOTES OF MEMBERS OF THE LEAGUE, AND THEIR SELF- GOVERNING DOMINIONS AND CALMIES.
TO RECESS UNTIL TOMORROW AT 11 A.M., MOTION MADE DURING DEBATE RELATING TO THE VERSAILLES TREATY.

TO RETURN TO THE CONSIDERATION OF LEGISLATIVE BUSINESS BEFORE THE SENATE, A MOTION MADE DURING DICUSSION ON AGREEING TO A COMMITTEE OF CONFERENCE REPORT ON HR 9205, THE SUPPLY DEFICIENCIES APPROPRIATION BILL FOR THE FISCAL YEAR ENDING JUNE 30, 1920.
TO PASS, OVER THE ACTS OF THE PRESIDENT, HR 6810, A BILL PROHIBITING INTOXICATION BEVERAGES AND CONTROLLING THE MANUFACTURE AND USE OF ALCOHOL.

TO AMEND THE VERSAILLES TREATY BY GIVING IMPERIAL AND FEDERAL GOVERNMENTS AND THEIR SELF-GOVERNING DOMAINS, AS MEMBERS OF THE LEAGUE OF NATIONS ONLY ONE MEMBERSHIP VOTE IN THE COUNCIL AND ONE VOTE AND THREE DELEGATES IN THE ASSEMBLY.
TO AGREE TO AN AMENDMENT OF THE COMMITTEE ON FOREIGN RELATIONS TO THE VERSAILLES TREATY DENYING VOTE IN THE ASSEMBLY TO NATIONS CONCERNED IN DISPUTE WITH EACH OTHER, WHO ARE MEMBERS OF THE LEAGUE.

TO TABLE AN AMENDMENT TO THE VERSAILLES TREATY INSERTING IN IN THE TREATY, THE FOLLOWING "INVOKE THE CONSIDERATE JUDGEMENT OF MANKIND AND THE GRACIOUS FAVOR OF ALMIGHTY GOD," IN ORDER TO POSTPONE FURTHER CONSIDERATION OF SAME.
TO AMEND THE VERSAILLES TREATY BY GIVING THE UNITED STATES A VOTING POWER EQUAL TO ANY LEAGUE MEMBER, IN COUNCIL, ASSEMBLY, ANY LABOR ORGANIZATION, OR CONFERENCE UNDER THE LEAGUE.
TO TABLE S. J. RES. 120, A RESOLUTION ASSURING THE NATIONAL ADMINISTRATION OF THE UNQUALIFIED SUPPORT OF CONGRESS IN DEALING WITH THE IMPENDING STRIKE OF THE COAL MINERS IN THE UNITED STATES.

TO AMEND THE VERSAILLES TREATY BY ELIMINATING ARTICLES 156 TO 158, COMPELLING GERMANY TO RENOUNCE TO JAPAN, ALL RIGHT, TITLE AND INTEREST WHICH GERMANY HERETOFORE HAD IN THE PROVINCE OF SHANTUNG, CHINA.
TO AMEND THE VERSAILLES TREATY BY STRIKING FROM THE TREATY THE PROVISION ON LABOR AND THEREBY ALLOWING THE UNITED STATE TO CONTINUE TO FORM ITS OWN LABOR POLICY.
TO AMEND THE VERSAILLES TREATY BY FORBIDDING ANY DECLARATION OF WAR WITHOUT A REFERENDUM AND APPROVING VOTE OF THE PEOPLE.

TO AMEND RESERVATION ONE OF THE VERSAILLE TREATY, BY MAKING RATIFICATION EFFECTIVE AND BINDING UPON THE UNITED STATE ONLY AFTER ADOPTION OF RESERVATIONS AND EXCHANGE OF NOTES BETWEEN THE UNITED STATES AND THE ALLIES.
TO AMEND THE VERSAILLES TREATY BY PROVIDING FOR THE DISPOSITION OF THE ENTIRE TREATY BY THE UNITED STATES UPON ACTION OF THE SENATE AMENDMENT.
TO AMEND RESERVATION NO. 1 TO THE VERSAILLES TREATY, BY REQUIRING THE ACTION OF THE FOUR PRINCIPAL ALLIED AND ASSOCIATED POWERS, UPON RESERVATIONS AND UNDERSTANDINGS ADOPTED BY THE SENATE.

TO AMEND RESERVATION NO. 1 OF THE VERSAILLES TREATY BY MAKING RATIFICATION INEFFECTIVE AND NOT BINDING UPON THE UNITED STATES UNTIL RESERVATION HAVE BEEN ADOPTED AND ACCEPTED BY AN EXCHANGE OF NOTES, OR RECOGNITION OF THE UNITED STATES AS A PARTY TO THE TREATY, BY AT LEAST THREE OF THE FOUR ALLIES, (GT. BRITAIN, FRANCE, ITALY, AND JAPAN).

TO AMEND RESERVATION NO. 1 OF THE VERSAILLES TREATY BY IMPOSING AS A CONDITION FOR OUR RATIFICATION OF THE TREATY, THE ACCEPTANCE OF THE RESERVATIONS PROPOSED IN OUR RESOLUTION OF RATIFICATION, BY AT LEAST THREE OF THE FOUR ALLIES.

TO AMEND THE 2ND RESERVATION OF THE VERSAILLES TREATY, BY PROVIDING THAT ANY NOTICE OF WITHDRAWAL OF THE UNITED STATES FROM THE LEAGUE OF NATIONS MAY BE GIVEN BY THE PRESIDENT OR BY A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION OF CONGRESS.
TO AMEND THE RESERVATION NO. 2 OF THE VERSAILLES TREATY, PROVIDING THAT WITHDRAWAL OF THE UNITED STATES FROM THE LEAQUE OF NATIONS MAY BE MADE BY THE PRESIDENT OR BY A JOINT RESOLUTION OF CONGRESS.

TO AMEND RESERVATION NO. 2 OF THE VERSAILLES TREATY, BY MAKING THE UNITED STATES SOLE JUDGE AS TO WHETHER ITS INTER- NATIONAL OBLIGATIONS HAVE BEEN FULFILLED, IN THE EVENT OF WITHDRAWAL FROM THE LEAGUE OF NATIONS.

TO AMEND RESERVATION NO. 2 TO THE VERSAILLES TREATY, BY MAKING ANY NATION SOLE JUDGE AS TO WHETHER ITS INTERNATIONAL OBLIGATIONS HAVE BEEN FULFILLED, IN THE EVENT OF ITS WITH- DRAWAL FROM THE LEAGUE OF NATIONS.

TO AGREE TO RESERVATION NO. 2 TO THE VERSAILLES TREATY, WHICH MAKES THE UNITED STATES THE SOLE JUDGE AS TO WHETHER ITS INTERNATIONAL OBLIGATIONS HAVE BEEN FULFILLED, IN THE EVENT OF WITHDRAWAL FROM THE LEAGUE OF NATIONS, AND THAT SUCH WITHDRAWAL MAY BE MADE BY A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION OF CONGRESS.

TO AMEND RESERVATION NO. 3 TO THE VERSAILLES TREATY, BY PROVIDING THAT ONLY BY ACTION OF CONGRESS, MAY THE UNITED STATES FORCES BE USED TO ENFORCE THE OBLIGATIONS OF ARTICLE TEN, AND THAT A REFUSAL TO DO SO SHALL NOT CONSTITUTE A VIOLATION OF THE TREATY.

TO AMEND RESERVATION NO. 3 TO THE VERSAILLES TREATY, BY RELEASING THE UNITED STATE FROM THE TERMS AND CONDITIONS OF ARTICLE TEN, WHICH OBLIGATES THE UNITED STATES TO ENTER EVERY WAR THAT MAY COME TO THE WORLD.

TO AMEND RESERVATION NO. 3 TO THE VERSAILLES TREATY BY PROHIBITING THE UNITED STATES FROM ASSUMING ANY OBLIGATION TO PRESERVE THE TERRITORIAL INTEGRITY OR POLITICAL INDEPENDENCE OF ANY COUNTRY AND FROM INTERFERING IN CONTRO- VERSIES BETWEEN NATIONS OR EMPLOYING NAVAL OR MILITARY FORCES UNLESS CONGRESS DECLARES WAR.

TO TABLE THE APPEAL OF SENATOR HITCHCOCK FROM THE CHAIRS DECISION, HOLDING HIS MOTION TO IMPOSE CLOTURE ON SENATE DEBATE ON VERSAILLES TREATY AND AMENDMENTS THERETO AS NOT IN ORDER, AND THEREBY UPHOLDING THE DECISION OF THE CHAIR.
TO AMEND RESERVATION 3 TO THE VERSAILLE TREATY, BY RELEASING ALL MEMBERS OF THE LEAGUE OF NATIONS FROM ANY OBLIGATION TO THE UNITED STATES UNDER ARTICLE TEN.

TO AMEND RESERVATION NO. 3 TO THE VERSAILLES TREATY, BY PROHIBITING THE UNITED STATES FROM ASSUMING ANY OBLIGATION, PENDING THE EXPIRATION OF FIVE YEARS FROM RATIFICATION OF THE TREATY, TO PRESERVE THE TERRITORIAL INTEGRITY OR POLITICAL INDEPENDENCE, OF ANY OTHER COUNTRY.

TO AMEND RESERVATION NO. 3 OF THE VERSAILLES TREATY, BY INTENDING FOR A FIVE YEAR PERIOD, THE OBLIGATION OF THE UNITED STATES TO POLAND, CZECHOSLAVOKIA, AND THE SERB-CROAT-SLOVENE STATE, CREATED BY THE TREATY.

TO AMEND RESERVATION NO. 3 OF THE VERSAILLES TREATY, BY EXTENDING THE OBLIGATION OF THE UNITED STATE AND OTHER LEAGUE OF NATIONS MEMBERS, FOR A FIVE YEAR PERIOD, TO THE FRENCH REPUBLIC IN MAINTAINING HER SOVEREIGNTY OVER ALSACE-LORRAINE.

TO SUBSTITUTE FOR RESERVATION NO. 3 TO THE VERSAILLES TREATY, A PROVISION THAT EACH MEMBER OF THE LEAGUE OF NATIONS IS FREE TO ACCEPT OR REJECT THE ADVICE OF THE COUNCIL REGARDING THE USE OF THEIR ARMED FORCES.

TO AMEND THE VERSAILLES TREATY, BY SUBSTITUTING FOR RESERVATION NO. 3 A PROVISION THAT THE UNITED STATES, IN ASSUMING THE OBLIGATION TO PRESERVE THE TERRITORIAL INTEGRITY, OR POLITICAL INDEPENDENCE OF ANY COUNTRY, OR IN INTERFERING IN CONTROVERSIES BETWEEN NATIONS, OR EMPLOYING MILITARY OR NAVAL FORCES, DOES SO SUBJECT TO THE JUDGEMENT AND ACTION OF CONGRESS.

TO AMEND RESERVATION NO. 3 TO THE VERSAILLES TREATY, BY ADDING AN ADDITIONAL CLAUSE DECLARING IT TO BE THE POLICY OF THE UNITED STATES GOVERNMENT TO REGARD ANY THREAT TO THE FREEDOM AND THE PEACE OF EUROPE, MADE BY ANY POWER OR COMBINATION OF POWERS, AS A MENACE TO ITS OWN PEACE AND FREEDOM, AND A CONSULTATION BETWEEN THE UNITED STATES AND AFFECTED POWERS WILL BE HELD TO DEVISE MEANS FOR REMOVAL OF SUCH MENACE.
TO AMEND THE VERSAILLES TREATY, BY PROVIDING THAT ONLY CONGRESS CAN DECIDE TO USE THE ARMED FORCES OF THE UNITED STATES.

TO TABLE THE APPEAL OF MR. LA FOLLETTE FROM THE CHAIRS DECISION TO CALL THE ROLL IN ORDER TO DETERMINE IF A QUORUM IS PRESENT, BEFORE SUBMITTING TO THE SENATE A MOTION SIGNED BY 16 SENATORS TO CLOSE DEBATE ON A RESOLUTION RELATING TO THE VERSAILLES TREATY.
TO ADOPT A MOTION FOR CLOTURE SIGNED BY 16 SENATORS TO BRING TO CLOSE THE DEBATE ON THE VERSAILLES TREATY.

TO AMEND THE TREATY OF PEACE WITH GERMANY BY PROVIDING THAT NO MEMBER NATION IS REQUIRED TO SUBMIT TO THE LEAGUE, ITS COUNCIL, OR ITS ASSEMBLY, FOR DECISION, REPORT, OR RECOMMENDATION, ANY MATTER WHICH IT CONSIDERS TO BE A DOMESTIC QUESTION, SUCH AS IMMIGRATION, LABOR, TARIFF, OR OTHER MATTERS RELATING TO ITS INTERNAL OR COASTWISE AFFAIRS.

TO AMEND RESERVATION NO. 5 TO THE VERSAILLES TREATY, THAT THE UNITED STATES RESERVES TO ITSELF EXCLUSIVELY THE RIGHT TO DECIDE WHAT QUESTIONS ARE WITHIN ITS DOMESTIC JURISDICTION, BY INCLUDING ALL QUESTIONS AFFECTING THE PRESENT BOUNDARIES OF THE UNITED STATES AND ITS INSULAR OR OTHER POSSESSIONS.

TO AGREE TO RESERVATION NO. 5, AS AMENDED, TO THE VERSAILLES TREATY PROVIDING THAT THE UNITED STATES RESERVES TO ITSELF EXCLUSIVELY THE RIGHT TO DECIDE WHAT QUESTIONS ARE WITHIN ITS DOMESTIC JURISDICTION, INCLUDING ALL QUESTIONS AFFECTING THE PRESENT BOUNDARIES OF THE UNITED STATES AND ITS INSULAR OR OTHER POSSESSIONS.

TO AGREE TO A SUBSTITUTE TO RESERVATION NO. 6 TO THE VERSAILLES TREATY, PROVIDING THAT THE NATIONAL POLICY OF THE UNITED STATES KNOWN IS THE MONROE DOCTRINE, SHALL IN NO WAY BE IMPAIRED OR AFFECTED BY THE COVENANT OF THE LEAGUE OF NATIONS, AND IS NOT SUBJECT TO ANY DECISION, REPORT OR INQUIRY BY THE COUNCIL OR ASSEMBLY OF THE LEAGUE.
TO AMEND RESERVATION NO. 6 TO THE VERSAILLE TREATY, BY PROVIDING THAT THE UNITED STATES SHALL NOT BIND ITSELF TO SUBMIT FOR ARBITRATION ANY QUESTIONS INVOLVING THE MONROE DOCTRINE.

TO ADOPT RESERVATION NO. 6 TO THE VERSAILLES TREATY, PROVIDING THAT THE UNITED STATES WILL NOT SUBMIT TO ARBITRATION OR TO INQUIRY BY THE ASSEMBLY OR COUNCIL OF THE LEAGUE OF NATIONS, ANY QUESTION RELATING TO THE MONROE DOCTRINE.

TO AGREE TO A SUBSTITUTE AMENDMENT TO RESERVATION NO. 7 OF THE VERSAILLE TREATY PROVIDING THAT THE UNITED STATE REFRAIN FROM ENTERING INTO ANY AGREEMENT REGARDING THE CONTROL OF THE PROVINCE OF SHANTUNG BY JAPAN, AND RESERVING FULL LIBERTY OF ACTION IN RESPECT TO ANY CONTROVERSY WHICH MAY ARISE IN RELATION THERETO.

TO AGREE TO AN AMENDMENT TO RESERVATION NO. 7 OF THE VERSAILLE TREATY, PROVIDING THAT IN CONSENTING TO THE TREATY'S RATIFICATION, THE UNITED STATE UNDERSTAND THAT GERMAN RIGHTS AND INTERESTS RENOUNCED IN FAVOR OF JAPAN UNDER THE TREATY, ARE TO BE RETURNED BY JAPAN TO CHINA.

TO AGREE TO RESERVATION NO. 7 OF THE VERSAILLES TREATY, PROVIDING THAT THE UNITED STATES WITHHOLD ITS ASSENT TO ARTICLES 156, 157 AND 158, AND RESERVE FULL LIBERTY OF ACTION WITH RESPECT TO ANY CONTROVERSY WHICH MIGHT ARISE UNDER SAID ARTICLES BETWEEN THE REPUBLIC OF CHINA AND THE EMPIRE OF JAPAN, REGARDING THE RIGHTS OF GERMAY IN CHINA, WHICH WERE RENOUNCED BY THIS TREATY TO JAPAN.

TO AGREE TO RESERVATION NO. 8 OF THE VERSAILLES TREATY, PROVIDING THAT ANY REPRESENTATIVE OF THE UNITED STATES TO THE LEAGUE OF NATIONS, OR TO ANY COUNCIL REGARDING THE TREATY, WILL BE APPOINTED UNDER THE LAW PROVIDED BY CONGRESS AND WITH THE APPROVAL OF THE SENATE.

TO AGREE TO RESERVATION NO. 9 OF THE VERSAILLES TREATY, PROVIDING THAT THE UNITED STATES UNDERSTANDS THAT THE REPARATION COMMISSION WILL REGULATE, OR INTERFERE WITH EXPORTS FROM THE UNITED STATES TO GERMANY, OR FROM GERMANY TO THE UNITED STATES ONLY WHEN THE UNITED STATES BY ACT OR JOINT RESOLUTION OF CONGRESS APPROVES SUCH REGULATION OR INTERFERENCE.

TO AGREE TO RESERVATION NO. 10 OF THE VERSAILLE TREATY, PROVIDING THAT THE UNITED STATES SHALL NOT BE OBLIGATED TO CONTRIBUTE TO ANY EXPENSES OF THE LEAGUE OF NATIONS, OR OF THE SECRETARIAT, OR OF ANY COMMISSION, COMMITTEE, CONFERENCE, OR AGENCY THEREOF, UNLESS AN APPROPRIATION OF FUNDS FOR SUCH EXPENSES SHALL HAVE BEEN MADE AVAILABLE BY CONGRESS.

TO AGREE TO RESERVATION NO. 10 OF THE VERSAILLES TREATY, PROVIDING THAT SHOULD A PLAN FOR THE LIMITATION OF ARMAMENTS, AS PROPOSED BY THE COUNCIL OF THE LEAGUE OF NATIONS, BE ADOPTED BY THE UNITED STATES, IT RESERVES THE RIGHT TO INCREASE SUCH ARMAMENTS WITHOUT THE CONSENT OF THE COUNCIL, IN CASE OF A THREAT OF INVASION OR THREAT OF WAR.

TO AGREE TO RESERVATION NO. 12 OF THE VERSAILLE TREATY, RESERVING TO THE UNITED STATES THE RIGHT TO PERMIT IN ITS DISCRETION THE NATIONALS OF A COVENANT BREAKING STATE, AS DEFINED IN ARTICLE 16 OF THE COVENANT OF THE LEAGUE OF NATIONS, RESIDING WITHIN THE UNITED STATES, OR IN COUNTRIES OTHER THAN THAT VIOLATING SAID ARTICLE 16, TO CONTINUE THEIR COMMERCIAL, FINANCIAL, AND PERSONAL RELATIONS WITH THE NATIONALS OF THE UNITED STATES.
TO AGREE TO RESERVATION NO. 13, OF THE VERSAILLES TREATY, SAFEGUARDING THE RIGHTS OF CITIZENS TO CONTEST ANY ACTION OR ORDER OF THE ALIEN PROPERTY CUSTODIAN IN OUR COURTS.

TO AGREE TO RESERVATION NO. 14 OF THE VERSAILLE TREATY, DECLARING THAT THE UNITED STATES DECLINES TO HAVE ANYTHING TO DO WITH THE FORMER OVERSEAS POSSESSIONS OF GERMANY, OR VOTE ON 548A IS MISNUMBERED.  Y=36 N=56 HODGE, TO AGREE TO RESERVATION 15, PROVIDING THAT U. S. RESERVES TO ITSELF EXCLUSIVELY THE RIGHT TO DECIDE WHICH QUESTION AFFECT ITS HONOR OR ITS TOTAL INTEREST TO ACCEPT AS A TRUSTEE ANY RESPONSIBILITY FOR THE GOVERNMENT OR DISPOSITION OFANY OF GERMANY'S OVERSEAS POSSESSIONS.

TO AGREE TO A RESERVATION OF THE VERSAILLES TREATY, WHICH DECLARES THAT THE UNITED STATES SHALL NOT RECOGNIZE THE PROTECTORATE OF GREAT BRITAIN OVER EGYPT, AND THAT IT UNDERSTANDS THIS PROTECTORATE TO BE MERELY A MEANS THOUGH WHICH THE NOMINAL SOVEREIGNTY OF TURKEY OVER EGYPT SHALL BE TRANSFERRED TO THE EGYPTIAN PEOPLE.

TO AGREE TO A RESERVATION TO THE VERSAILLE TREATY, RESERVING TO THE UNITED STATES THE RIGHT TO DECIDE ALL QUESTIONS RELATIVE TO ITS INTERNAL AFFAIRS AND DECLINING TO PARTICIPATE IN ANY WAY IN THE GENERAL CONFERENCE, OR IN THE ELECTION OF THE GOVERNING BODY OF THE INTERNATIONAL LABOR OFFICE, AND DECLINING TO CONTRIBUTE TO THE EXPENDITURES OF THE SAME.
TO AGREE TO RESERVATION NO. 7 OF THE VERSAILLE TREATY, PROVIDING THAT THE UNITED STATES SHALL NOT PARTICIPATE IN THE INTERNATIONAL LABOR OFFICE, UNLESS CONGRESS SHALL MAKE PROVISION FOR THE SAME.
TO AGREE TO A SUBSTITUTE AMENDMENT TO THE VERSAILLES TREATY, PROVIDING FOR EQUAL REPRESENTATION AND EQUAL VOTING POWER OF OUR COUNTRY ALONG WITH GREAT BRITAIN IN THE LEAGUE OF NATIONS.

TO AGREE TO RESERVATION NO. 15 OF THE VERSAILLES TREATY, RESERVING TO THE UNITED STATES THE RIGHT TO DECIDE WHAT QUESTIONS AFFECT ITS HONOR AND INTEREST AND PROVIDING THAT SUCH QUESTION SHALL NOT BE SUBMITTED TO ARBITRATION OR TO THE COUNCIL OF THE LEAGUE OF NATIONS.

TO AGREE TO A SUBSTITUTE RESERVATION TO THE VERSAILLES TREATY, DECLARING THAT THE UNITED STATES ASSUMES NO OBLIGATION TO BE BOUND BY ANY ELECTION OR FINDING BY THE LEAGUE IN WHICH ANY MEMBER OF THE LEAGUE, AND ITS SELF GOVERNING DOMINIONS IN THE AGGREGATE HAVE CAST MORE THAN ONE VOTE; AND PROVIDING THAT THE CONSENT OF THE UNITED STATES MUST BE RECEIVED TO ALLOW A MEMBER WITH SELF GOVERNING DOMINIONS TO CAST MORE THAN ONE VOTE ON ANY QUESTION AFFECTING THE UNITED STATES.

TO AGREE TO A SUBSTITUTE RESERVATION TO THE VERSAILLES TREATY, DECLARING THAT THE UNITED STATES ASSUMES NO OBLIGATION TO BE BOUND BY ANY DECISION OR REPORT OF THE LEAGUE OF NATIONS, IN WHICH ANY MEMBER OF THE LEAGUE, AND ITS SELF GOVERNING DOMINIONS IN THE AGGREGATE HAVE CAST MORE THAN ONE VOTE AND ALSO ASSUMES NO OBLIGATION TO BE BOUND BY ANY DECISION ARISING OUT OF ANY DISPUTE BETWEEN THE UNITED STATES AND ANY MEMBER OF THE LEAGUE IN WHICH SAID MEMBER OR ANY OF ITS SELF GOVERNING DOMINIONS HAVE VOTED.

TO AGREE TO A RESERVATION OF THE VERSAILLES TREATY, RESERVING TO THE UNITED STATES THE RIGHT TO INTERPRET THE COVENANT OF THE LEAGUE AND THE VERSAILLES TREATY IN HARMONY WITH THE PRESIDENT'S FOURTEEN POINTS AND PROVIDING THAT THE UNITED STATES DOES NOT CONSIDER ITSELF BOUND TO ANY LINE OF CONDUCT, MILITARY OR FINANCIAL, IN CONFLICT THEREWITH.

TO AGREE TO A RESERVATION TO THE VERSAILLES TREATY, PROPOSING TO ACCOMPLISH TWO PURPOSES:  THE ESTABLISHMENT OF PEACE WITH GERMANY, AND A REASONABLE AND TOLERABLE PARTICIPATION IN THE MATTER OF INDEMNITIES.

TO AGREE TO A RESERVATION OF THE VERSAILLES TREATY, PROVIDING THAT THE REPRESENTATIVE OF THE UNITED STATES ON THE COUNCIL OF THE LEAGUE OF NATIONS SHALL NOT GIVE HIS CONSENT TO ANY PROPOSAL WHICH MAY INVOLVE THE USE OF MILITARY OR NAVAL FORCES OF THE UNITED STATES UNTIL SUCH PROPOSAL SHALL BE SUBMITTED TO CONGRESS FOR AUTHORITY.

TO AGREE TO A RESERVATION TO THE VERSAILLES TREATY, PROVIDING THAT NOTHING CONTAINED IN THE PROPOSED TREATY, OR COVENANT SHALL BE SO CONSTRUED AS TO REQUIRE THE UNITED STATES TO DEPART FROM THE TRADITIONAL POLICY OF NOT ENTANGLING ITSELF IN THE INTERNAL AFFAIRS OF ANY FOREIGN STATE.

TO AGREE TO A RESERVATION TO THE VERSAILLES TREATY, PROVIDING THAT THE UNITED STATES SHALL AT ANY TIME HAVE THE PRIVILEGE OF NOMINATING ANY NON-MEMBER NATION OF THE WORLD FOR LEAGUE MEMBERSHIP AND IN THE CASE OF UNFAVORABLE ACTION TAKEN BY THE LEAGUE, THE UNITED STATES RESERVES THE RIGHT TO WITHDRAW AS A MEMBER WITHOUT NOTICE.

TO AGREE TO RESERVATION NO 1 OF THE VERSAILLES TREATY, PREVENTING THE UNITED STATES FROM BEING OBLIGATED TO HELP GREAT BRITAIN PUT DOWN A REBELLION IN IRELAND, INDIA, EGYPT, OR ELSEWHERE, OR TO HELP JAPAN OR ANY OTHER COUNTRY ENGAGED IN EXPLOITING WEAKER OR LESS WARLIKE PEOPLE.

TO AGREE TO RESERVATION NO. 2 OF THE VERSAILLE TREATY, PROVIDING THAT THE UNITED STATES HEREBY GIVES NOTICE THAT IT WILL WITHDRAW FROM THE LEAGUE OF NATIONS AT THE END OF ONE YEAR FROM THE DATE OF EXCHANGE OF RATIFICATIONS, UNLESS WITHIN THAT TIME EACH MEMBER OF THE LEAGUE SHALL ABOLISH AND DISCONTINUE THE POLICY OF MAINTAINING ITS ARMY OR NAVY IN TIME OF PEACE BY CONSCRIPTION.

TO AGREE TO RESERVATION NO. 3 TO THE VERSAILLES TREATY, PROVIDING THAT THE UNITED STATES HEREBY GIVES NOTICE THAT IT WILL WITHDRAW FROM THE LEAGUE OF NATIONS AT THE END OF FIVE YEARS FROM THE DATE OF THE EXCHANGE OF RATIFICATIONS OF THE TREATY, UNLESS WITHIN THAT TIME EACH MEMBER SHALL HAVE AGREED THAT IN NO CASE WILL IT RESORT TO WAR, EXCEPT TO SUPPRESS AN INSURRECTION OR REPEL AN ACTUAL INVASION OF ITS TERRITORY.

TO AGREE TO RESERVATION NO. 4 OF THE VERSAILLES TREATY, PROVIDING THAT THE UNITED STATES HEREBY GIVES NOTICE THAT IT WILL WITHDRAW FROM THE LEAGUE OF NATIONS, IF ANY MEMBER SPENDING MORE THAN FIFTY MILLION DOLLARS A YEAR FOR ITS ARMY AND A LIKE SUM FOR ITS NAVY, SHALL FAIL TO REDUCE THE EXCESS BY 1/5 A YEAR, SO THAT AT THE END OF FIVE YEARS NO MEMBER SHALL BE SPENDING MORE THAN THE SAID FIFTY MILLION DOLLARS A YEAR.

TO AGREE TO RESERVATION NO. 5 OF THE VERSAILLES TREATY, PROVIDING THAT THE UNITED STATE WILL WITHDRAW FROM THE LEAGUE OF NATIONS, WHENEVER ANY MEMBER SHALL ATTEMPT TO ACQUIRE ANY TERRITORY OF ANY MEMBER OR NON-MEMBER, WITHOUT THE FULL AND FREE CONSENT OF THE PEOPLE RESIDING IN SAID TERRITORY.

TO AGREE TO RESERVATION NO. 6 OF THE VERSAILLES TREATY, PROVIDING THAT THE UNITED STATES WILL WITHDRAW FROM THE LEAGUE OF NATIONS WHENEVER ANY MEMBER EXERCISING A MANDATE OR PROTECTORATE OVER ANY COUNTRY SHALL, WITHOUT THE FREE AND FULL CONSENT OF THE PEOPLE OF SUCH COUNTRY, ATTEMPT TO ACQUIRE THE TITLE TO THE NATURAL RESOURCES OR RIGHTS TO THE PROPERTY, OR SHALL FAIL TO EXERCISE ITS MANDATE OVER SUCH A COUNTRY FOR THE SALE BENEFIT OF THE PEOPLE.

TO AGREE TO A RESERVATION TO THE VERSAILLES TREATY, PROVIDING THAT ARTICLE NO. 11 SHALL IN NO RESPECT ABRIDGE THE RIGHT OF FREE SPEECH, THE LIBERTY OF THE PRESS, AND THE ADVOCACY OF THE PRINCIPLES OF NATIONAL INDEPENDENCE OF ANY PEOPLE, AND NO CIRCUMSTANCE RELATING TO THE ENJOYMENT OF ANY OF THE AFORESAID RIGHTS SHALL BE CONSTRUED TO ALLOW THE ASSEMBLY OF THE LEAGUE TO DETERMINE WHAT COURSE OF ACTION, LEGAL MEASURES OF CONTROL, OR REGULATION SHALL BE ENFORCED OR PRESCRIBED BY THE UNITED STATES.

TO CONCUR IN RESERVATION NO. 4 TO THE VERSAILLES TREATY, PROVIDING THAT NO MANDATE SHALL BE ACCEPTED BY THE UNITED STATES UNDER PROVISIONS OF THE TREATY EXCEPT BY ACTION OF CONGRESS.

TO AGREE TO RESERVATION NO. 15 OF THE VERSAILLE TREATY, RESERVING TO THE UNITED STATES THE EXCLUSIVE RIGHT OF SELF- DETERMINATION THOSE QUESTIONS THAT AFFECT ITS HONOR OR VITAL INTEREST AND THAT SUCH QUESTIONS SHALL NOT BE SUBMITTED TO THE LEAGUE OF NATIONS FOR DECISION
